{"title":"(21) implementacion-amb-sysmayal2 - Raven","url":"https://erp.sysmayal2.cloud/raven/AMB-Wellness/AMB-Wellness-implementacion-amb-sysmayal2","summary":"This is a technical support channel for AMB Wellness implementation discussing bug fixes for the QTN-0754 pipeline (Sales Order to Invoice creation). The channel contains a detailed troubleshooting conversation about fixing two bugs: 1) Preview returning True instead of formatted message, and 2) mode_of_payment MandatoryError when creating Sales Invoices. The development team identified root causes, deployed multiple hotfixes, and eventually resolved both issues by removing duplicate code paths in command_router.py so invoice commands route to sales.py which has all required CFDI features. The final test was successful, creating Sales Invoice ACC-SINV-2026-00009 with all CFDI fields properly set.","key_points":["Message 1 (09:46 PM) - Administrator Technical Support: Test results for Agent Fixes for QTN-0754 Pipeline - Commits tested c486bbd, 0271988, 7e736c3 - Bug 1: Preview returns True instead of formatted message - Bug 2: MandatoryError mode_of_payment blocking SI creation","Message 2 (09:49 PM) - User: @ai invoice from SO-00754-Calipso s.r.l","Message 3 (09:49 PM) - sales_order_bot: Preview showing CFDI: PPD | G01 | Wire Transfer with Use ! to confirm","Message 4 (09:50 PM) - User: @ai !invoice from SO-00754-Calipso s.r.l","Message 5 (09:50 PM) - sales_order_bot: Error - mode_of_payment MandatoryError for ACC-SINV-2026-00007","Message 6 (09:51 PM) - Administrator Technical Support: Hotfix deployed - Commit 9405165 fixes mode_of_payment - mode_of_payment needs to be injected BEFORE frappe.get_doc() call","Message 7 (09:56 PM) - Administrator Technical Support: Test Results Round 2 - Preview PASS, Execute STILL FAILING - Root cause: command_router.py routes to workflows.py NOT sales.py - workflows.py missing mode_of_payment, debit_to, conversion_rate, mx_product_service_key, party_account_currency","Message 8 (10:00 PM) - Administrator Technical Support: Summary - Bug 1 (preview) already fixed in previous hotfix - Bug 2 root cause: make_sales_invoice() returns dict without CFDI fields, si.set() silently fails","Message 9 (10:03 PM) - User: @ai invoice from SO-00754-Calipso s.r.l","Message 10 (10:03 PM) - sales_order_bot: Preview with CFDI: PPD | G01 | Wire Transfer","Message 11 (10:03 PM) - User: @ai !invoice from SO-00754-Calipso s.r.l","Message 12 (10:03 PM) - sales_order_bot: Error - mode_of_payment for ACC-SINV-2026-00008","Message 13 (10:04 PM) - Administrator Technical Support: Test Results Round 3 - Fix applied to WRONG FILE (sales.py vs workflows.py) - command_router.py line 138 always routes invoice from SO to workflows.py - Fix needed in workflows.py lines 308-314","Message 14 (10:08 PM) - Administrator Technical Support: Correct Fix - commit d82eb1d applied to workflows.py - Applies all 3 CFDI fields using .update() + setattr()","Message 15 (10:09 PM) - Administrator Technical Support: Fix Option B - commit 1ebd6f5 - Remove lines 132-139 from command_router.py - Invoice commands now fall through to sales.py with all 6 CFDI features","Message 16 (10:10 PM) - User: @ai invoice from SO-00754-Calipso s.r.l","Message 17 (10:10 PM) - sales_order_bot: Preview with full details - Customer: Calipso s.r.l, Total: USD 69,189.12, CFDI: PPD | Use: G01 | Pay: Wire Transfer","Message 18 (10:11 PM) - User: @ai !invoice from SO-00754-Calipso s.r.l","Message 19 (10:11 PM) - sales_order_bot: SUCCESS - Sales Invoice ACC-SINV-2026-00009 created - Total: USD 69,189.12, CFDI: PPD | Use: G01 | Pay: Wire Transfer, TC: 17.7962 (banxico_fix)","Message 20 (10:12 PM) - Administrator Technical Support: TEST RESULTS ROUND 4 - ALL PASS - SI created with all CFDI fields: mode_of_payment Wire Transfer, mx_payment_option PPD, mx_cfdi_use G01, conversion_rate 17.7962, debit_to CALIPSO sub-account 1105.2.85, party_account_currency MXN, mx_product_service_key 31151517 - Pipeline QTN-0754 COMPLETED"],"relevant_links":["https://erp.sysmayal2.cloud/app/sales-invoice/ACC-SINV-2026-00009"],"file_name":"raven_channel_messages_implementacion_amb_sysmayal2.json"}
